headers.name: EVA-User-Agent
headers.description: The user agent that is making these calls. Don't make this specific per device/browser but per application. This should be of the form: `MyFirstUserAgent/1.0.0`

headers.name: EVA-Requested-OrganizationUnitID
headers.description: The ID of the organization unit to run this request in.

headers.name: EVA-Requested-OrganizationUnit-Query
headers.description: The query that selects the organization unit to run this request in.

headers.name: EVA-IDs-Mode
headers.description: The IDs mode to run this request in. Currently only `ExternalIDs` is supported.

headers.name: EVA-IDs-BackendSystemID
headers.description: The ID of the backend system that is used to resolve the IDs.

B.name: AutoShipAfterConfirm
B.description: When the created payment is confirmed and the order is paid, the order will be shipped automatically when possible.

B.name: CurrencyID
B.description: If the payment is done in another currency than the Order, this is required

F.name: DateTimeValue
F.description: Used for datatype DateTime and Date

F.name: NumberValue
F.description: Used for datatype Integer and Decimal

F.name: StringValue
F.description: Used for datatype String, Text and Enum

BE.name: DisplayOnTerminal
BE.description: If the current station terminal should be instructed to show this QR code, too.

BE.name: ReturnUrl
BE.description: ReturnUrl where the customer should be redirected to after the payment.

BE.name: SendEmail
BE.description: If an email with payment information should be sent.

BE.name: SendEmailTo
BE.description: When `SendEmail` is true, but `SendEmailTo` is omitted, a fallback to the Order.Customer.EmailAddress is attempted.

BR.name: Code
BR.description: A unique ID identifying this error.

BR.name: Message
BR.description: A human-readable message describing the error.

BR.name: RequestID
BR.description: A unique ID identifying the request. Please provide this ID when contacting support.

BR.name: Type
BR.description: A short description of the error type.

BS.name: ExternalIDs
BS.description: When using the `ExternalIDs` mode, this will hold the resolved external IDs.

BS.name: IsAsyncResultAvailable
BS.description: This is a flag indicating whether the async request is done. If it is `null`, it is not an async service. If it is `false`, the response is not yet available. Do not process the properties in that case. It is is `true` the properties are filled with the result of the call.

BS.name: UnresolvedExternalIDs
BS.description: When using the `ExternalIDs` mode, this will hold the external IDs we couldn't resolve.
